<row>
<entry valign="top">Corporation</entry>
<entry valign="top"><list list-type="bulleted" id="list-00005">
<item>Limited liability protects owners from losing more than they invest.</item>
<item>Can achieve large size due to marketability of stock (ownership).</item>
<item>Receives certain tax advantages.</item>
<item>Greater access to financial resources allows growth.</item>
<item>Can attract employees with specialized skills.</item>
<item>Ownership is readily transferable.</item>
<item>Long life of firm (not affected by death of owners).</item></list></entry>
<entry valign="top"><list list-type="bulleted" id="list-00006">
<item>More expensive and complex to form.</item>
<item>Subject to more government regulation.</item>
<item>Financial reporting requirements make operations public.</item>
<item>Double taxation because both corporate profits and dividends paid to owners are taxed, although the dividends are taxed at a reduced rate.</item>
</list></entry>
